I can't remember what prompted this unwonted early Queen move, when f3 looked such an attractive square for the Nd2.  Perhaps I planned a quick Qg3, attacking g7 and vacating the f3 square for the N.  For now, though, the Q interferes with the development of White's minor Q-side pieces.
